column2: loon pair and what looked to be young calling and body posturing- kingfisher pair with two young learning how to fish around Belle Point.
young eagle flying and trying landings at various big pines

This was a non-satellite day but we were out to take a sample for water chemistry and measured temperature and secchi. It was cloudy and breezy and we had had several days of high winds and below-normal temperatures. The air temperature was mid-50s and the surface water temperature (according to Michael's fish finder) was 60. We had a hard time believing our water temperature readings so we did it twice and had the same numbers both times.
Weather was sunny but very windy and the surface of the lake was a little choppy. Air temperature was in the low 60's.
